entries_unprocessed.text: I went to a party. I was super anxious because my friend Allie was mad at me. She said I am the worst and terrible. I felt sad. My friend Henry cheered me up. At the start it was hard. But when I started to dance, I was able to have fun and let go. I love dancing. It makes me feel so free and lovely.

I was stressed all day because of a test coming up. Allie said I was going to do terrible and I am the stupidest person she has ever met. I cried in the library bathroom. I really think I will fail it and there is nothing I can do. Math is so hard. Math ruins my life. At least Henry had dinner with me and reminded me I was smart. He was a happy party of my day.
I did so well on my math test! I was super surprised! Allie was mad I did better than her. But she did not make me feel bad. I felt empowered. The sun was shining and it was a very happy day.
